parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission shifting issues can cause hesitation, surging, and loss of power, leading to accidents or near-misses.
Unintended acceleration can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: and failure to respond to brake input.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause loss of power, stalling, and accidents.
Clutch issues can cause difficulty shifting, loss of power, and accidents.
Software issues can cause transmission problems, hesitation, and loss of power.
symptoms: and loss of power after software updates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended acceleration of the vehicle can cause accidents, injuries, and fatalities, as well as damage to property.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and unexpectedly
often when the driver is attempting to slow down or stop
and may continue to accelerate even when the brake pedal is pressed. In some cases
the vehicle may surge forward or backward without warning
and the driver may be unable to control the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electronic throttle control can cause the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle may experience sudden and unexpected acceleration
often when the driver is attempting to slow down or stop. The vehicle may also stall or hesitate when accelerating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake pedal can cause the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal may feel soft or spongy
and the vehicle may not respond to brake pedal input. In some cases
the vehicle may accelerate even when the brake pedal is pressed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: and/or fails to stop when brakes are applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake failure can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The brakes fail to stop the vehicle
and/or the vehicle vibrates when brakes are applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Warped brake rotors can cause vibration when braking, leading to loss of vehicle control and accidents.
symptoms: causing vibration when brakes are applied
and/or the vehicle experiences extended stopping distance.
